==English==

===Etymology===
Latin ''[[realitas]]'' from [[real]] + [[-ity]]

===Pronunciation===
*{{IPA|/ɹiˈæləti/}}, {{SAMPA|/r\i"{l@ti/}}
*{{audio|en-us-reality.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Noun===
'''reality'''
#The entirety of all that is real.
#Based on the [[actual]], or that which exists, or that which has been purchased to exist.
#That which is ultimately foundational beyond all words or concepts. That which is beyond what is perceived, and yet is apprehended to contain all that ever can be perceived.

